sive investigation into the origins, development, and impact of Canada's space program. Through meticulous research, including newly declassified material, it demonstrates the central role of the military in Canada's early space research. Moreover, it reveals the technological, political, and strategic implications of the country's early innovation in space-research technology, and its subsequent turn from this arena. A striking contribution to Canada's military and political history, Defence and Discovery illuminates a significant yet understudied period in Canada's growth as a nation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAstronautics, Military -- Canada -- History. 0aCanada -- History, Military -- 20th century. 0aOuter space -- Exploration -- Canada -- History. 7aHISTORY / Military / Weapons.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077481961940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774819619423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774819619/original  a978-3-11-127414-0  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-127721-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles